        <active>true</active>
        <article><![CDATA[<p>Set the <em>x_taniu_tan_core.tanium_api_token</em> system property to the API Token for the Tanium service account.<br />You can read about how to generate an API Token in the <a title="Tanium documentation" href="https://docs.tanium.com/platform_user/platform_user/console_api_tokens.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">Tanium documentation</a>.</p>
<p>When generating an API Token for ServiceNow, be sure to set the <strong>Expiration</strong> to 365 days, and set the <strong>Trusted IP addresses</strong> to &#34;0.0.0.0/0&#34;, <em>or</em> to the CIDR range of your ServiceNow environment. You can find this range by contacting ServiceNow support or through the ServiceNow support portal. This is important, since your ServiceNow instance doesn&#39;t typically have a single or necessarily static IP address.</p>
<p>This system property is stored using 2-way encryption so that it&#39;s encrypted at rest. </p>]]></article>
